1. "When finding minimums or maximums, initialize with the extreme opposite bound so the first real candidate replaces it."
    int minLength = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
    int count = 0;

2. Edge Cases :
    - Input size : 
        - null/empty input
        - single element
        - max possible size
    - Input values :
        - negative numbers
        - very large numbers
        - floating point numbers
    - Special arrangements :
        - already sorted
        - reverse sorted
        - duplicate numbers
    - Invalid Inputs : 
        - Null pointers
        - Malformed inputs
